{"id":1947,"date":"2020-11-03T10:09:10","date_gmt":"2020-11-03T10:09:10","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/parliament.imarketing.com.na\/?page_id=1947"},"modified":"2021-05-05T02:27:56","modified_gmt":"2021-05-05T00:27:56","slug":"outreach","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/outreach\/","title":{"rendered":"Outreach"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>[vc_row][vc_column css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1620174473947{background-color: #f4f4f4 !important;}&#8221;]<div id=\"ultimate-heading-22516848a4c823ee2\" class=\"uvc-heading ult-adjust-bottom-margin ultimate-heading-22516848a4c823ee2 uvc-2083  uvc-heading-default-font-sizes\" data-hspacer=\"no_spacer\"  data-halign=\"left\" style=\"text-align:left\"><div class=\"uvc-heading-spacer no_spacer\" style=\"top\"><\/div><div class=\"uvc-main-heading ult-responsive\"  data-ultimate-target='.uvc-heading.ultimate-heading-22516848a4c823ee2 h2'  data-responsive-json-new='{\"font-size\":\"\",\"line-height\":\"\"}' ><h2 style=\"font-weight:bold;\">The Outreach Programs of Parliament<\/h2><\/div><\/div>[vc_column_text]The Parliament of Namibia as part of its mandate of enhancing public understanding of the parliamentary process and increasing public participation in the law-making process designed two types of outreach programs to achieve its objectives:[\/vc_column_text]<div id=\"ultimate-heading-25976848a4c823f26\" class=\"uvc-heading ult-adjust-bottom-margin ultimate-heading-25976848a4c823f26 uvc-9305  uvc-heading-default-font-sizes\" data-hspacer=\"no_spacer\"  data-halign=\"left\" style=\"text-align:left\"><div class=\"uvc-heading-spacer no_spacer\" style=\"top\"><\/div><div class=\"uvc-main-heading ult-responsive\"  data-ultimate-target='.uvc-heading.ultimate-heading-25976848a4c823f26 h2'  data-responsive-json-new='{\"font-size\":\"\",\"line-height\":\"\"}' ><h2 style=\"font-weight:bold;\">a) \u201cTaking Parliament to the People\u201d<\/h2><\/div><\/div>[vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This program is conducted by Presiding Officers and MPs assisted by the staff. The program is aimed at bridging the gap between Parliamentarians and the public as well as getting MPs to familiarise themselves with development taking place in the country.<br \/>\nIt consists of three sub-programs:<\/p>\n<ol>\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Speaker\u2019s\/Chairperson&#8217;s (Presiding Officers) Outreach Program, \u201cConsulting Constituencies on service delivery\u201d.<\/li>\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Public Hearings<\/li>\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Committees regional Visits<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text]<div id=\"ultimate-heading-64786848a4c823f4e\" class=\"uvc-heading ult-adjust-bottom-margin ultimate-heading-64786848a4c823f4e uvc-7986  uvc-heading-default-font-sizes\" data-hspacer=\"no_spacer\"  data-halign=\"left\" style=\"text-align:left\"><div class=\"uvc-heading-spacer no_spacer\" style=\"top\"><\/div><div class=\"uvc-main-heading ult-responsive\"  data-ultimate-target='.uvc-heading.ultimate-heading-64786848a4c823f4e h2'  data-responsive-json-new='{\"font-size\":\"\",\"line-height\":\"\"}' ><h2 style=\"font-weight:bold;\">b) Civic Education, \u201cImparting Parliamentary Knowledge<\/h2><\/div><\/div>[vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This program is conducted by officials from the Division: Research and Information Services of both Houses and is aimed at disseminating the parliamentary information to the public and to improve their understanding of Parliament, governance and democracy.<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Program consists of the following:<\/p>\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">School Program<\/li>\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Participation in Tertiary Education and Regional Education Career Fairs<\/li>\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Participation at\u00a0 Local Trade Fairs<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The principle of democracy is that people should have a say in what happens and what is decided. It is by participating in democracy that they play their role as citizens of the country. Public participation gives people opportunity and power to influence and understand the decisions that affect their lives.<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Namibian public remains apathetic towards the legislature and rarely participates in the law-making process, hence the importance of Parliament to engage the public through a strategic and well-thought public education programme in order to empower the people with the necessary information that will enable them to participate in decision-making and be active stakeholders in the law-making processes.<\/p>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text]<div id=\"ultimate-heading-17566848a4c823f72\" class=\"uvc-heading ult-adjust-bottom-margin ultimate-heading-17566848a4c823f72 uvc-3725  uvc-heading-default-font-sizes\" data-hspacer=\"no_spacer\"  data-halign=\"left\" style=\"text-align:left\"><div class=\"uvc-heading-spacer no_spacer\" style=\"top\"><\/div><div class=\"uvc-main-heading ult-responsive\"  data-ultimate-target='.uvc-heading.ultimate-heading-17566848a4c823f72 h2'  data-responsive-json-new='{\"font-size\":\"\",\"line-height\":\"\"}' ><h2 style=\"font-weight:bold;\">The Mandate<\/h2><\/div><\/div>[vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Divisions: Research and Information Services are responsible for conducting\u00a0<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/index.php\/visitorsss\/tours\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">tours<\/a>\u00a0of Parliament and civic education activities, by promoting and disseminating educational information to the public.<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Different outreach programs have been designed and conducted by the Parliament of Namibia since &#8211; 2000. These include:<\/p>\n<ol>\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">School- Education program<\/li>\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Tertiary Education Campuses program<\/li>\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Participation at Local Trade and Career Fairs<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][\/vc_row]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>[vc_row][vc_column css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1620174473947{background-color: #f4f4f4 !important;}&#8221;][vc_column_text]The Parliament of Namibia as part of its mandate of enhancing public understanding of the parliamentary process and increasing public participation in the law-making process designed two types of outreach programs to achieve its objectives:[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text] This program is conducted by Presiding Officers and MPs assisted by the staff. The program is aimed&hellip;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":8,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":[],"class_list":["post-1947","page","type-page","status-publish","hentry","description-off"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/1947","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/page"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/8"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=1947"}],"version-history":[{"count":20,"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/1947\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":4218,"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/1947\/revisions\/4218"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=1947"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}